Ask HN: Any note-taking software that has AsciiDoc support?
text: The market is filled with note-taking apps, knowledge bases, second brains, etc. in which you can write notes in Markdown. How about AsciiDoc? It's better in quite a few aspects, though not gaining much popularity. Anchors can be put pretty much anywhere, and linking to them seems more natural than "backlinks". Complete table support. Also has native admonitions.
